                            </origPlace>
                            <origDate source="TRE1985">Second quarter of the eighth century</origDate>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance type="found" when="1911">Originally the front panel of an altar, this incised slab was discovered at Ballavarkish keeill (IOMHER 0402.00) during excavations undertaken by the Manx Archaeological Survey in 1911. The ogham was first mentioned by Kermode (1911, 53-76) in PSAS, although the ogham was not shown in the published drawing.
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed">Now in the Manx Museum.
                        </provenance>
